==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Laystall
<hw>Lay"stall`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A place
where rubbish, dung, etc., are laid or deposited.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Smithfield was a <qex>laystall</qex> of all ordure and filth.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place where milch cows are kept, or cattle on the
way to market are lodged.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lazar</ent>⟦br⟧
